high.mackenzie.autumn.lang.compiler.typesystem.design

Interface ITypeFactory

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    TypeFactory

    public interface ITypeFactory
    An instance of this interface is a factory that produces type objects and components therefor.

      • getArrayType

        IArrayType getArrayType(IElementType element,
                      int dimensions)
        This method returns the type of an array, given its element-type and dimensions.
        Parameters:
        element - is the type of the elements in an array of the returned type.
        dimensions - is the number of dimensions in an array of the returned type.
        Returns:
        the aforedescribed array-type.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if(element == null)
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if(dimensions < 1)

      • fromClass

        IType fromClass(java.lang.Class<?> clazz)
        This method finds and returns a type, given its java.lang.Class representation.
        Parameters:
        clazz - is the class-object representation of the type to find.
        Returns:
        the aforedescribed type, or null, if no suitable type can be found.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if(clazz == null)

      • findType

        IType findType(java.lang.String name)
        This method finds and returns a type, given its name.

        The following types of types can be found:

        • Primitive Types
        • Void IType
        • Null IType
        • Previously Manufactured - Class Types
        • Previously Manufactured - Interface Types
        • Previously Manufactured - Enum Types
        • Previously Manufactured - Array Types
        • Class.forName(name)

        Parameters:
        name - is the name of the type to find.
        Returns:
        the aforedescribed type, or null, if no suitable type can be found.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if(name == null)

      • getTypes

        java.util.Collection<IType> getTypes()
        This method returns all the type objects that have been created by this factory.
        Returns:
        an immutable collection containing the products of this type-factory.
